<subSubSection id="51C0CE9C40592C12F285D038E5C731BE" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" type="notes">
<paragraph id="CD4EC0815A953640B1701D969FD9A43C" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A20C31C3C8DCBB713B5AA3701395CC6C" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
This species is characterized by non-ostiolate ascomata and ellipsoidal to fusiform ascospores ornamented with wing-like appendages and wrinkles, and the production of a phialidic asexual morph and bulbils. 
<taxonomicName id="2161CE8EE3213E4D0C954477DC41602B" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Ceratostomataceae" genus="Microthecium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Microthecium lenticulare" order="Melanosporales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="lenticulare">Microthecium lenticulare</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="024863C145272D02E79F8FEF599633DC" genus="Mi." lsidName="Mi. foveolatum" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" rank="species" species="foveolatum">Mi. foveolatum</taxonomicName>
also present ascospores with wing-like appendages, but these are pitted and not wrinkled (as in 
<taxonomicName id="420846CD05C85351E1CD228556BC153E" genus="Mi." lsidName="Mi. ciliatum" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" rank="species" species="ciliatum">Mi. ciliatum</taxonomicName>
), and neither species produces bulbils. 
<taxonomicName id="26360BC65071A92E342B19B29038C1B0" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Ceratostomataceae" genus="Microthecium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Microthecium foveolatum" order="Melanosporales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="foveolatum">Microthecium foveolatum</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="E7DB887B6B77A4E58454B2361112C153" genus="Mi." lsidName="Mi. ciliatum" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" rank="species" species="ciliatum">Mi. ciliatum</taxonomicName>
are characterized by non-ostiolate ascomata and the production of a phialidic asexual morph, whereas 
<taxonomicName id="E6931B94C5DBB6AC7056611FA73E256C" genus="Mi." lsidName="Mi. lenticulare" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" rank="species" species="lenticulare">Mi. lenticulare</taxonomicName>
has ostiolate ascomata and lacks an asexual morph.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
